ation: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000=
000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">But, no</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In a surprise move that sent shockwaves throug=
hout the junior Wall Street community on Monday, a series of leading privat=
e-equity firms kicked off recruiting for lucrative positions that won't sta=
rt for two more years.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The intense rite of passage known as "on-cycle=
 recruiting" left some junior investment bankers scrambling to get in on a =
flurry of hastily arranged interviews. It marked buy-side recruiting's earl=
iest start date on record. The cycle had shifted progressively earlier in r=
ecent years. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Most first-year investment-banking analysts wo=
n't officially start their banking roles until July. The early recruiting t=
imeline has left most candidates with no real-life deal experience to speak=
 of, let alone workplace experience to point to, beyond their past summer i=
nternships. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This year, two sources said that the unexpecte=
d start meant that some incoming junior bankers were outside New York City.=
 Some soon-to-be bankers, they added, haven't even moved into their New Yor=
k City apartments yet.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That is from a Business Insider article that q=
uotes a junior banker from=C2=A0<em>last=C2=A0</em>year=E2=80=99s PE recrui=
ting cycle saying =E2=80=9Chonestly, it has been making me think that priva=
te equity, especially, is just such an abusive industry,=E2=80=9D and decid=
ing not to go into private equity at all. I suppose the counterpoint is: Ye=
s, that=E2=80=99s what it=E2=80=99s=C2=A0<em>supposed=C2=A0</em>to do. If y=
ou=E2=80=99re not willing to drop everything to fly to New York ahead of yo=
ur investment banking start date to do private equity recruiting, will you =
drop everything to fly across the country to close a deal as a private equi=
ty employee? Making recruiting stressful and inconvenient probably does mak=
e it more informative; it tells you something about the candidate=E2=80=99s=
 dedication and performance under stress. And what else do the firms have t=
o go on? It=E2=80=99s not like these people have done any deals.</p>
